  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Before and during bariatric surgery patients are given oral and i.v. midazolam, respectively
      and blood samples are drawn to establish midazolam time-concentration profiles. After 0.5-2
      years, and substantial weight loss, oral and i.v. midazolam are administered once more and
      blood samples are taken again.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
